obo:ECO_0006042  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_1406  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Authors investigate whether Htt plays a role in transporting NF-kB from the postsynaptic compartment to the nucleus based on the fact that Htt interacts preferable with the active form of NF-kB. They performed photo activation experiments in primary hippocampal cultures of control and conditional htt knockout mice and observed that when htt was missing the half-life of NF-kB movement was double as compared to control mice. This data was in agreement with the quantification of NF-kB levels in the nucleus fraction prepared from control and knockout mice, which showed significantly lower levels in the absence of htt.. Experimental description: From results:\n\"nuclear fractions prepared from forebrains of (A) 4-month-old Htt knock-out (KO) and control (CTRL) mice (n 1/4 2 non-sex matched, littermate pairs) and (B) 6-month-old HD knock-in (HD) and wild- type control (WT) mice (n 1/4 2 non-sex matched, littermate pairs). See text for quantification of the immunoblots.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0575-6950" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1585-539X" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-16" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1406" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

